      <div xml:id="NA319-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu kāppu mikutikkaṇ āṟṟāṉāki talaimakaṉ talaimakaḷai niṉaintu taṉṉuḷḷē colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what HE who was unable to bear it during the increase of guarding said to his own heart when thinking of HER.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA319">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            ōtamu moliyō viṉṟē yūtaiyun</l>
<l>            tātuḷar kāṉaṟ ṟavveṉ ṟaṉṟē</l>
<l>            maṇaṉmali mūtū rakaṉeṭun teruviṟ</l>
<l>            kūkaic cēval kurālō ṭēṟi</l>
<l>            yāriruñ catukkat tañcuvarak kuḻaṟu</l>
<l>            maṇaṅkukāl kiḷaru mayaṅkiru ṇaṭunāṭ</l>
<l>            pāvai yaṉṉa palarāy vaṉappiṟ</l>
<l>            ṟaṭameṉ paṇaittōṇ maṭamiku kuṟumakaḷ</l>
<l>            cuṇaṅkaṇi vaṉamulai muyaṅka luḷḷi</l>
<l>            mīṉkaṇ ṭuñcum poḻutum</l>
<l>            yāṉkaṇ ṭuñcēṉ yātuko ṉilaiyē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>The sound of the flood has stopped,</l>
<l rend="indent4">and the cold wind,</l>
<l>whiffling pollen has come down intensely<note place="foot">Here we clearly have an ideophone and a transmissional problem, namely four different versions of the semantically irreducible part. "<term xml:lang="ta">tav</term>" is certainly the lectior facilior, but it is the only one that makes sense to me, since there is a parallel in KT 356 where it obviously conveys intensity.</note> on the seashore grove.</l>
<l rend="indent">At diffuse dark midnight, when the time of torments comes up,</l>
<l rend="indent2">where the cock of the owl rises with [its] female(?)<note place="foot">Actually, the text just gives two different words for owl (or two different kinds of owl): <term xml:lang="ta">kūkai</term> and <term xml:lang="ta">kurāl</term>, but the topos clearly demands a couple.</note></l>
<l rend="indent3">in the wide long streets of the old village full of sand</l>
<l rend="indent2">[and] shrieks on the difficult dark junctions for fear to come,</l>
<l>my<note place="foot">Here we have a breach of morphology for the sake of analogy: <term xml:lang="ta">mīṉ kaṇ tuñcum - yāṉ kaṇ tuñcēṉ</term>, the latter being a conflation of "I do not sleep" with "my eyes do not sleep".</note> eyes don’t sleep,</l>
<l rend="indent">at the time when the fish eyes are sleeping,</l>
<l rend="indent2">in the remembrance of embracing the beautiful breast adorned</l>
<l rend="indent2">with spots of the little woman full of inexperience,</l>
<l rend="indent2">with broad soft bamboo shoulders,</l>
<l rend="indent3">of a beauty appreciated by many, like an image.</l>
<l rend="indent4">What [is this] state?</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
